WITH prices rising quickly, people in Mzansi are feeling the pinch. More people need to dip into credit to survive sooner and sooner after pay day. Susan Steward, marketing manager of Budget Insurance, said: “It’s easy to neglect our saving and budgeting goals. “If you change the way you do things and plan your spending wisely, you can get or stay out of debt and do much more than just survive.” Here are Steward’s tips to help you with your money: Try creating a weekly meal plan, buying in bulk and stocking up on discounted items. If you want to use an app, make sure it is from a reliable source. Remove it if you suspect anything. Sometimes it is safer to write your budget on paper.